# Deploy SafeSite AI — Vercel (Frontend) + Render (Backend) + MongoDB Atlas

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Vercel (Free)"] -->|"API calls"| B["Render (Free)"]
    B -->|"Read/Write"| C["MongoDB Atlas (Free)"]
    
    A -->|"Serves"| D["HTML, CSS, JS, Images"]
    B -->|"Serves"| E["FastAPI + YOLO + OpenCV"]

    style A fill:#000,stroke:#fff,color:#fff
    style B fill:#4F46E5,stroke:#fff,color:#fff
    style C fill:#00684A,stroke:#fff,color:#fff
```

**How it works:**
- User visits your Vercel URL → gets the static frontend instantly (no cold start)
- Frontend JS makes API calls to your Render backend URL for data/video processing
- Backend reads/writes to MongoDB Atlas (cloud database)
- Locally, you keep using `localhost:27017` (Compass) — the code auto-switches based on env vars

