## Proposed Changes

### Step 1: Create the Vercel frontend directory

We need a new `frontend/` folder at the project root with static HTML files (converted from Jinja2 templates). The only Jinja2 feature used is `{{ v }}` for cache busting — we'll replace that with a JS-based approach.

#### Directory structure:
```
frontend/              ← NEW (deployed to Vercel)
├── index.html         ← converted from templates/index.html
├── monitor.html       ← converted from templates/livemonitor.html
├── alerts.html        ← converted from templates/alert.html
├── analytics.html     ← converted from templates/analytics.html
├── about.html         ← converted from templates/about.html
├── contact.html       ← converted from templates/contact.html
├── static/
│   ├── css/           ← copied from website/static/css/
│   ├── js/            ← copied from website/static/js/ (with API URL changes)
│   └── images/        ← copied from website/static/images/
├── vercel.json        ← Vercel routing config
└── package.json       ← minimal, for Vercel detection
```

**Changes needed in HTML files:**
- Remove `?v={{ v }}` cache busting → Vercel handles caching automatically
- Nav links: `/monitor` → `monitor.html`, `/alerts` → `alerts.html`, etc.

**Changes needed in JS files:**
- All `/api/...` calls → `https://YOUR-RENDER-URL.onrender.com/api/...`
- WebSocket URL → `wss://YOUR-RENDER-URL.onrender.com/ws/detections`
- Video feed URL → `https://YOUR-RENDER-URL.onrender.com/api/video-feed`
- We'll use a single `config.js` file with the backend URL so it's easy to change

